			<body><div id="62--the-mound-by-the-lake">
				<pb facs="/images/battle-pieces-v1/battle-pieces-i-0179.jpg"/>
				<head type="main">
				<hi rend="italic">The Mound by the Lake.</hi>
				</head>
				<head type="sub-head"><hi rend="italic"></hi>
				</head>

<lg>
<l><hi rend="smallcaps">The</hi> grass shall never forget this grave.</l>
<l>When homeward footing it in the sun</l>
<l rend="2em">After the weary ride by rail,</l>
<l>The stripling soldiers passed her door,</l>
<l n="5" rend="2em">Wounded perchance, or wan and pale,</l>
<l>She left her household work undone—</l>
<l>Duly the wayside table spread,</l>
<l rend="2em">With evergreens shaded, to regale</l>
<l>Each travel-spent and grateful one.</l>
<l n="10">So warm her heart—childless—unwed,</l>
<l>Who like a mother comforted.</l>
</lg>

</div></body>
